<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-30T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-30T10:00:00-05:00" n="932" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d932">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/19096:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kelley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-30T17:00:00+02:00">January
                                    30, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 8:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>58. I have been informed by a person in confidence of President that
                            latter was very much pleased with Ambassador MacMurray’s interview in
                            Baltimore <hi rend="italic">Sun</hi> and considers it an excellent
                            expose of Turkey’s position.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kelley</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>